    <introduction>
      <para>Welcome to the Windows Installer XML (WiX) Sample.</para>
    </introduction>
    <section>
      <title>What this Sample Shows</title>
      <content>
        <para>This samples shows the following features of XML Schema Documenter:</para>
        <list class="bullet">
          <listItem>
            <para>
              Using an XSLT transform to incorparate existing custom inline documentation. Among others
              the WiX documents remarks and references to both other WiX elements as well as MSDN online
              topics about Windows Installer actions and tables. Examples include the
              <xsd:xmlEntityReference>http://schemas.microsoft.com/wix/2006/wi#E/AppId</xsd:xmlEntityReference>
              and the
              <xsd:xmlEntityReference>http://schemas.microsoft.com/wix/2006/wi#E/Class</xsd:xmlEntityReference>
              element.
            </para>
          </listItem>
          <listItem>
            <para>
              Using the <codeInline>parent</codeInline> element to document schema extensions. See for example
              the
              <xsd:xmlEntityReference>http://schemas.microsoft.com/wix/2006/wi#E/Component</xsd:xmlEntityReference>
              element which has many element extensions or the
              <xsd:xmlEntityReference>http://schemas.microsoft.com/wix/2006/wi#E/Extension</xsd:xmlEntityReference>
              element which has an attribute extension.
            </para>
          </listItem>
          <listItem>
            <para>
              Using an additional external documentation file for documenting the schema set.
            </para>
          </listItem>
          <listItem>
            <para>
              How documentation for a (mostly)
              <externalLink>
                <linkText>salami slice</linkText>
                <linkUri>http://blogs.msdn.com/skaufman/archive/2005/04/25/411809.aspx</linkUri>
              </externalLink>
              schema design looks like.
            </para>
          </listItem>
        </list>
      </content>
    </section>
